Introduction

Base URL: http://localhost

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

Display a listing of the resource.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/brand" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/brand"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

GET api/brand

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Store a newly created resource in storage.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/brand" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"brand_name\": \"lmjyvudnguabwjt\",
    \"email\": \"wbechtelar@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"nXz|\\\"H?\\/q>21uhkF\\\"~b\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/brand"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "brand_name": "lmjyvudnguabwjt",
    "email": "wbechtelar@example.com",
    "password": "nXz|\"H?\/q>21uhkF\"~b"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/brand

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

brand_name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: lmjyvudnguabwjt

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: wbechtelar@example.com

password   string    21uhkF"~b" data-component="body">

Must be at least 6 characters. Example: nXz|"H?/q>21uhkF"~b

Display the specified resource.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/brand/BRD01" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/brand/BRD01"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):

Show headers 
cache-control: no-cache, private
